We are parents of kids who are deaf or hard of hearing, including ASL and other visual-language signers, children who use listening and spoken language, cued speech users, total communicators, children with hearing aids or cochlear implants, and children who do not use technology to hear.

Hands & Voices is a safe place to explore options, get unemotional support, learn from one another, and share what we have in common. We value diversity and honor parents and family as the greatest factor in raising a well-adjusted, successful child.
